review 2: a very good location to spend the evening. It is highly recommended to come there on Saturday night because there will be several events. and also culinary spots for typical Balinese food.
review 3: This site is not finished yet. The statue of Bung Karno is not attached yet. Large parking area with well green maintained plantation. Mango and durian trees can be seen in this park. There is amphitheatre with large wing lion statue which is still under construction. Good place for jogging and may be an ideal place for entertainment show in the future and. Hopefully this site will be finished soon.
review 4:
spacious, with 2 tall statues, Soekarno, Indonesia's first president, and Singaraja's iconic lion statue.

A local spot to jog, picnic with family or friends. The water fountain is people's favorite spot. Today, 30 March, Marks the opening of rth Bung Karno.
review 5: If you want to know more about the first President of Indonesia, this place is recommended. There is a big monument in the middle of the park written some spirit of life during the period of pre-independence.
